---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import siteData from '../data/site.json';

const page = siteData.pages.services;
const styles = [
  'assets/css/tokens.css',
  'assets/css/interior-base.css',
  'assets/css/layout.css',
  'assets/css/components.css',
  'assets/css/services.css',
];
---
<Base
  title={page.title}
  description={page.description}
  canonical={page.canonical}
  subtitle={page.subtitle}
  eyebrow={page.eyebrow}
  introKicker={page.introKicker}
  introTitle={page.introTitle}
  introText={page.introText}
  currentNav={page.currentNav}
  styles={styles}
>
  <section class="reading-width stack">
    <article class="card stack">
      <p class="section-copy">The press's editorial practice and its advisory work derive from the same discipline: taking the formal properties of a problem seriously before proposing anything. The same habits that produce a coherent publishing program, rigorous selection, resistance to trend, accountability to a long horizon rather than a near one, produce useful advisory work for organizations that need careful judgment at consequential moments.</p>
      <p class="section-copy">A small number of external engagements, taken selectively. The number is small by design.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="services-grid">
    <article class="card service-card">
      <h3>Editorial strategy</h3>
      <p>Coherent long-form editorial positioning, publishing strategy, and public-facing narrative discipline for organizations that need it.</p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>Editorial architecture and publishing programs</li>
        <li>Message discipline for serious organizations</li>
        <li>Decision support for complex editorial choices</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="card service-card">
      <h3>Ontology and knowledge design</h3>
      <p>Structured knowledge modeling for projects that require traceable definitions, explicit relationships, and auditable reasoning. The same attention to definition the press brings to its critical and editorial work, applied to systems where the stakes make rigor non-optional.</p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>Ontology design and taxonomy work</li>
        <li>Knowledge graph and semantic modeling advisory</li>
        <li>Schema strategy for high-consequence systems</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="card service-card">
      <h3>Decision-intelligence systems</h3>
      <p>Design and review for explainable workflows where accountability, provenance, and governance take precedence over novelty.</p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>Auditable AI workflows</li>
        <li>Risk-aware decision support</li>
        <li>Governance and review structures</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="card service-card">
      <h3>Engagement model</h3>
      <p>Services are selective and scoped deliberately. Use About to describe the institution, the decision environment, and the outcome required.</p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>One or two engagements taken at a time</li>
        <li>Scoped per project, not retainer-based</li>
        <li>Direct correspondence, no intake forms</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/about">Discuss a project</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <Fragment slot="scripts">
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/site-shell.js" type="module"></script>
  </Fragment>
</Base>
